article.headline: Moody scores 21 to lead Montana past San Jose State 86-75
article.description: — Aanen Moody's 21 points helped Montana defeat San Jose State 86-75 on Sunday night.
article.linkText: Moody scores 21 to lead Montana past San Jose State 86-75
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- — Aanen Moody's 21 points helped Montana defeat San Jose State 86-75 on Sunday night. Moody added eight rebounds for the Grizzlies (6-4). Laolu Oke added 16 points while going 5 of 8 and 6 of 7 from the free throw line, and they also had 15 rebounds. Money Williams had 15 points and shot 4 of 8 from the field and 7 for 8 from the line. Myron Amey Jr. led the Spartans (6-6) in scoring, finishing with 15 points, four assists and three steals. Tibet Gorener added 13 points for San Jose State. Latrell Davis also had 12 points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
